Meet <b>Akima</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Akima lives at <a href='/home/?user=akima2sweet'>7561 Maple Street</a>, in the classy area of Westridge! She has a great view of all Millsberry from the windows of her house, which sits atop King's Hill. If you are visiting the area, you'll be able to recognize her home as the blue one in Westridge's newest neighborhood.<br><br>Akima is a very smart girl, who does well in school. She's also totally friendly too, which makes her a very popular person at the Academy. Akima is quite athletic as well. She is in great shape, and very healthy.<br><br>In school, Akima really enjoys writing, which helps her to do well in English class. She likes writing so much, in fact, that she even enjoys spending her time writing things that have nothing to do with her schoolwork. Maybe she'll become a great author someday!<br><br>During her spare time, Akima also enjoys playing all sorts of games. More often than not, she usually plays with a pair of headphones on, as she happens to be a big fan of music, too. Her favorite types are rap, reggae, and rhythm & blues.<br><br>After school, Akima can frequently be found lounging around the pool with her friends. Once they've soaked in some sun, they'll head off to the mall, and maybe pick up some new CDs. When shopping, Akima is always on the lookout for merchandise that is dark blue, pink, or light blue, because those are her favorite colors.<br><br>After a fun afternoon, Akima and her friends will sometimes head downtown, to the Millsberry Entertainment Complex,and catch the latest movie. Oddly though, the last time they went, someone with a crazy hat that looked like rabbit ears sat in front of them. Oh well? silly things will sometimes happen in Millsberry, but that's what makes living here so fun!</div>
